by:\nAttacks listed in Levels 1, 2, and 4 of this policy.\nTargeted insults.\nStatements wishing them death or serious illness, disability, epidemic disease, or physical harm.\nLevel 2: Targeting individuals, narrow public figures (for example, people known primarily for their activism or journalism, or those who become inadvertently famous), or public figures who are minors by:\n\nStatements wishing them death or contracting or developing a disease.\nInsults related to the female gender when used in a pejorative manner.\nStatements related to sexual activity or sexually transmitted diseases, except in the context of criminal charges against adults due to non-consensual sexual contact.\nPages or groups created to attack through:\nTargeted insults.\nNegative physical descriptions.\nStatements regarding religious identity or blasphemy.\nExpressions of contempt or disgust.\nInsults related to the female gender when used in a pejorative manner.\nLevel 3: Targeting public figures by deliberately exposing them to the following:\n\nFor adults and minors:\nStatements wishing them death or that they contract or develop a disease.\nStatements about sexually transmitted diseases.\nInsults related to the female gender when used in a pejorative manner.\nContent applauding, celebrating or ridiculing their death or a disease.\nAttacks based on negative physical descriptions.\nFor minors:\nComparisons with animals or insects that are culturally perceived as intellectually or physically inferior or with inanimate objects (for example: cow, monkey or stone).\nContent manipulated to highlight, emphasize, or draw negative attention to specific physical features (nose, ears, etc.).\nLevel 4: Targeting individuals, narrow public figures (e.g., people known primarily for their activism or journalism, or those who become famous unintentionally) by:\n\nComparisons to animals or insects that are culturally perceived as intellectually or physically inferior, or to inanimate objects (e.g., cow