tity or blasphemy.\nComparisons to animals or insects that are not culturally perceived as intellectually or physically inferior (e.g., tiger or lion).\nPositive or neutral physical descriptions.\nNon-negative statements related to people\'s character or abilities (e.g., regarding mental illness).\nAny violation of bullying or harassment policies, when shared in a positive context.\nAttacks using derogatory terms related to lack of sexual activity.',
